{"name": "kennypavan", "metadata": {"name": "KennyPavan", "version": "1.0.1", "classifiers": ["License :: OSI Approved :: MIT License", "Operating System :: OS Independent", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3"], "home_page": "https://github.com/kennypavan/kennypavan", "license": null, "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": [], "summary": "Kenny Pavan: About, projects, and resume as a PyPi package.", "upload_time": 1734391411}, "documentation": ["# Because it was too easy to just make this a pdf. \nBelow is a simple package which has methods for displaying details about my experience, skills, hobbies, current projects, some inspirational quotes, and resume. \n\n## Install\n```\npip install kennypavan\n```\n\n## Usage\n```python\nfrom KennyPavan import KennyPavan\n\n#treating myself as an object\nkp = KennyPavan()\n\n#about me\nkp.about()\n\n#skillset\nkp.skills()\n\n#experience\nkp.experience()\n\n#education\nkp.education()\n\n#show any publications\nkp.publications()\n\n```\n\n<br />\n\n## Displaying all\n```python\nfrom KennyPavan import KennyPavan\nkp = KennyPavan()\nkp.displayAll()\n```\n\n<br />\n<br />\n\n<font size=\"18px\">\ud83e\udd37</font><br />\n<i>There's also a few properties</i>\n"], "modules": [{"name": "KennyPavan.KennyPavan", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [{"name": "KennyPavan.KennyPavan.KennyPavan", "bases": [], "methods": [{"name": "KennyPavan.KennyPavan.KennyPavan.__init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "KennyPavan.KennyPavan.KennyPavan.displayAll", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "KennyPavan.KennyPavan.KennyPavan.about", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "KennyPavan.KennyPavan.KennyPavan.education", "asynchro